1. *Ratni* zločini ne smeju ostati nekažnjeni. (War crimes must not go unpunished.)
2. Njihov *ratni* zločin bio je stravičan. (Their war crime was horrific.)
3. *Ratni* veterani su se okupili kako bi obeležili godišnjicu bitke. (War veterans gathered to commemorate the anniversary of the battle.)
4. Upravo je izašla nova knjiga o *ratnom* vazduhoplovstvu. (A new book on military aviation has just been released.)
5. Mnoge zgrade su pretrpele *ratna* oštećenja tokom konflikta. (Many buildings suffered war damage during the conflict.)
6. *Ratni* zločinac je konačno uhvaćen i predat sudu. (The war criminal was finally captured and handed over to the court.)
7. Ova regija ima dugu istoriju *ratovanja*. (This region has a long history of warfare.)
8. Pored *ratnih* dešavanja, ima i mnogo drugih tema o kojima treba razgovarati. (Besides war-related issues, there are also many other topics to discuss.)
9. *Ratne* operacije su uvek rizične i zahtevaju dobru pripremu. (Military operations are always risky and require good preparation.)
10. Učesnici u *ratu* suočavaju se sa mnogim izazovima i teškoćama. (War participants face many challenges and difficulties.)

Note: In Serbian, the word "ratni" is an adjective that means "war-related", while the noun "rat" means "war".